<!-- ==================== 1. PROJECT OVERVIEW ==================== -->
<h1>1. Project Overview</h1>
<p>
    Sporshow is a multi-vendor e-commerce online marketplace where customers shop across multiple seller stores, sellers manage their own product catalogs and orders, a delivery manager coordinates the logistics network, and a platform admin oversees the entire marketplace. The system covers the full commerce cycle: product discovery, purchase, fulfilment, delivery, and post-purchase reviews.
</p>
<p>
    The platform is built using <strong>PHP</strong> for all server-side logic and <strong>MySQL</strong> as the database engine. It follows the <strong>MVC (Model-View-Controller)</strong> architectural pattern ensuring a clean separation of concerns between business logic, data access, and presentation layers. All database interactions use <strong>mysqli with prepared statements</strong> to prevent SQL injection attacks.
</p>

<h2>Platform Roles</h2>
<table>
    <tr><th>Role</th><th>Responsibility</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Customer</td><td>Browse, cart, checkout, track, review, wishlist</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Seller/Vendor</td><td>Product management, order fulfilment, analytics</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Delivery Manager</strong></td><td><strong>Agent management, order dispatch, delivery tracking</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Platform Admin</td><td>Seller approval, categories, disputes, platform reports</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="page-break"></div>

<!-- ==================== 2. ROLE DESCRIPTION ==================== -->
<h1>2. Role Description &mdash; Delivery Manager</h1>
<p>
    The Delivery Manager is responsible for the entire logistics network of the Sporshow marketplace. This role maintains a pool of delivery agents operating across Bangladesh (primarily Dhaka and surrounding divisions), assigns incoming orders to available agents based on delivery zone and agent availability, monitors all active deliveries in real time, and provides operational summaries of delivery performance.
</p>
<p>
    The Delivery Manager has their own dedicated portal with a sidebar navigation system, a real-time logistics dashboard, and full CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) capabilities for managing agents and delivery zones. The portal also includes an AJAX-powered delivery status update system that allows status changes without page reloads.
</p>

<div class="page-break"></div>

<!-- ==================== 3. FEATURES ==================== -->
<h1>3. Features Implemented</h1>

<h2>3.1 Login &amp; Authentication</h2>
<p>
    The Delivery Manager logs in through a dedicated login page using their registered email and password. The system authenticates the user by verifying the provided credentials against the <code>users</code> table using PHP's <code>password_verify()</code> function with bcrypt hashing. Upon successful login, a PHP session is created storing the user's ID, name, email, and role.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Role-based access control (RBAC)</strong> is enforced on every protected page. The <code>requireRole('delivery_manager')</code> middleware function checks that the logged-in user has the correct role. If an unauthorized user attempts to access any delivery manager page, they receive a 403 Access Denied response.
</p>
<p>
    The login form includes both <strong>client-side JavaScript validation</strong> (checking for empty fields before submission) and <strong>server-side PHP validation</strong> (verifying credentials and role). Descriptive error messages are displayed for invalid credentials.
</p>

<h2>3.2 Logistics Dashboard</h2>
<p>Upon logging in, the Delivery Manager is presented with a logistics dashboard that displays key operational metrics at a glance:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Pending Dispatch Count:</strong> Number of orders with &lsquo;shipped&rsquo; status that have not yet been assigned to any delivery agent.</li>
    <li><strong>Active Deliveries:</strong> Number of delivery assignments currently in progress (assigned, picked up, or in transit).</li>
    <li><strong>Delivered Today:</strong> Number of deliveries successfully completed on the current date.</li>
    <li><strong>Total Agents:</strong> Total number of delivery agents registered in the system, with a count of currently active agents.</li>
</ul>
<p>The dashboard also provides <strong>quick action links</strong> for navigating to dispatch orders, viewing active deliveries, managing agents, and managing zones.</p>

<h2>3.3 Delivery Agent Management</h2>
<p>The Delivery Manager can manage the pool of delivery agents with full CRUD operations:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Add New Agent:</strong> Register a new delivery agent with their name, phone number, and vehicle type (Motorcycle, Van, Bicycle, or Car).</li>
    <li><strong>Edit Agent:</strong> Modify an existing agent's details including name, phone, and vehicle type.</li>
    <li><strong>Activate/Deactivate Agent:</strong> Toggle an agent's active status. Deactivated agents cannot be assigned to new deliveries.</li>
    <li><strong>View All Agents:</strong> Display a comprehensive table showing all agents with their ID, name, phone, vehicle type, number of currently active deliveries, and status (active/inactive).</li>
</ul>

<h2>3.4 Delivery Zone Management</h2>
<p>Delivery zones represent the geographic areas where orders can be delivered. Each zone has a name, delivery fee (in BDT), and estimated delivery time in days.</p>
<table>
    <tr><th>Zone</th><th>Delivery Fee (BDT)</th><th>Estimated Days</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Dhaka City</td><td>60.00</td><td>1</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Gazipur</td><td>100.00</td><td>1</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Narayanganj</td><td>100.00</td><td>1</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Chattogram</td><td>150.00</td><td>2</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Sylhet</td><td>180.00</td><td>3</td></tr>
</table>
<p>The Delivery Manager can <strong>add</strong>, <strong>edit</strong>, and <strong>delete</strong> delivery zones.</p>

<h2>3.5 Order Dispatch</h2>
<p>The Dispatch Orders page shows all orders that are <strong>ready for dispatch</strong> &mdash; orders where the seller has confirmed and shipped their items (status = &lsquo;shipped&rsquo;) but no active delivery agent has been assigned yet. The Delivery Manager selects an agent and a zone, then clicks Assign.</p>

<h2>3.6 Active Delivery Tracking</h2>
<p>The Active Deliveries page displays all deliveries currently in progress with their order ID, customer name, zone, assigned agent, current status, and time of assignment.</p>

<h2>3.7 AJAX Status Update (XMLHttpRequest Feature)</h2>
<p>The delivery status update feature is implemented using <strong>AJAX (XMLHttpRequest)</strong>. This allows the Delivery Manager to update a delivery's status (Picked Up &rarr; In Transit &rarr; Delivered) <strong>without reloading the page</strong>. The JavaScript sends a request to a PHP API endpoint which returns a JSON response, and the page updates dynamically.</p>

<h2>3.8 Failed Delivery Handling</h2>
<p>When a delivery cannot be completed, the Delivery Manager can mark it as failed with a reason, or re-assign it to a different agent through a popup modal.</p>

<h2>3.9 Delivery History</h2>
<p>A complete record of all completed and failed deliveries with full timestamps and failure reasons.</p>

<h2>3.10 Daily &amp; Weekly Delivery Summary</h2>
<p>Aggregated statistics showing total delivered, total failed, and total in transit for today and this week.</p>

<h2>3.11 Profile Management</h2>
<p>Upload profile picture, update personal information, and change password with proper validation.</p>

<div class="page-break"></div>

