<!-- ==================== 6. TECHNICAL DETAILS ==================== -->
<h1>6. Technical Implementation Details</h1>

<h2>6.1 Authentication &amp; Session Management</h2>
<p>Authentication is handled through PHP sessions. The <code>config/auth.php</code> file provides helper functions: <code>isLoggedIn()</code>, <code>requireLogin()</code>, and <code>requireRole($role)</code>. Every controller calls <code>requireRole('delivery_manager')</code> before executing. Passwords use bcrypt hashing via <code>password_hash()</code> and <code>password_verify()</code>.</p>

<h2>6.2 Prepared Statements</h2>
<p>All database queries use <strong>mysqli prepared statements</strong> with parameter binding to prevent SQL injection. No raw string concatenation is used in any SQL query.</p>

<h2>6.3 AJAX Implementation</h2>
<p>The AJAX feature uses <code>XMLHttpRequest</code> to send POST requests to <code>api/update_delivery_status.php</code>, which returns JSON. The page updates dynamically without reloading.</p>

<h2>6.4 Validation</h2>
<p><strong>Client-side:</strong> JavaScript validates forms before submission (empty checks, password matching, confirm dialogs).</p>
<p><strong>Server-side:</strong> PHP validates all inputs again (empty checks, type casting, file extension checks, password length). User output is escaped with <code>htmlspecialchars()</code> to prevent XSS.</p>

<div class="page-break"></div>

<!-- ==================== 7. SETUP GUIDE ==================== -->
<h1>7. How to Run the Project (Setup Guide)</h1>

<h2>Prerequisites</h2>
<ul>
    <li>XAMPP installed (includes Apache, MySQL, and PHP)</li>
    <li>A web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Step 1: Install XAMPP</h3>
<p>Download from <strong>https://www.apachefriends.org/</strong> and install with default settings.</p>

<h3>Step 2: Start Apache and MySQL</h3>
<p>Open XAMPP Control Panel. Click <strong>"Start"</strong> next to both <strong>Apache</strong> and <strong>MySQL</strong>.</p>

<h3>Step 3: Copy Project Files</h3>
<p>Copy the entire project folder into the <code>htdocs</code> directory:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Windows:</strong> <code>C:\xampp\htdocs\</code></li>
    <li><strong>Mac:</strong> <code>/Applications/XAMPP/htdocs/</code></li>
</ul>

<h3>Step 4: Create the Database</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Open browser &rarr; go to <strong>http://localhost/phpmyadmin</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>"SQL"</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Copy contents of <code>sql/schema.sql</code> &rarr; paste &rarr; click <strong>"Go"</strong></li>
</ol>

<h3>Step 5: Import Seed Data</h3>
<ol>
    <li>In phpMyAdmin, click <strong>"SQL"</strong> tab again</li>
    <li>Copy contents of <code>sql/seed.sql</code> &rarr; paste &rarr; click <strong>"Go"</strong></li>
</ol>

<h3>Step 6: Open the Application</h3>
<p>Navigate to: <strong>http://localhost/Sporshow%20Web%20Tech%20Project/</strong></p>

<h3>Troubleshooting</h3>
<table>
    <tr><th>Issue</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Database connection error</td><td>Ensure MySQL is running. Check <code>config/database.php</code> credentials.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Page not found</td><td>Ensure project is in <code>htdocs/</code> and Apache is running.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Login fails</td><td>Re-run <code>seed.sql</code> in phpMyAdmin.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Profile picture upload fails</td><td>Ensure <code>uploads/profiles/</code> directory exists.</td></tr>
</table>

